# =============================================================================
# CYBERDUDEBIVASH AI Security Hub — Cloudflare Pages Redirect Rules v2.0
#
# ROOT CAUSE FIX (ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS):
#   Page-specific "200 rewrite" rules (e.g. /privacy-policy → /privacy-policy.html)
#   were conflicting with Cloudflare Pages' Automatic Clean URL feature:
#     1. /privacy-policy → _redirects 200 rewrite → internal fetch /privacy-policy.html
#     2. Cloudflare Pages auto-clean-URL strips .html → 301 redirect to /privacy-policy
#     3. Browser follows 301 → back to step 1 → infinite loop
#
# FIX: Remove ALL page-specific rewrite rules AND the SPA catch-all.
#   Cloudflare Pages routing order:
#     ① Exact static file match
#     ② _redirects rules  ← we only place static asset guards here
#     ③ Clean URL lookup: /privacy-policy → privacy-policy.html (native, no redirect)
#     ④ 404
#   Step ③ handles ALL clean-URL page requests correctly with zero redirect hops.
#
# All links on this platform already use .html extensions.
# Direct .html access (e.g. /privacy-policy.html) triggers Cloudflare's own
# one-time 301 to /privacy-policy — correct, no loop.
#
# Rule format: [source] [destination] [status_code]
# 200 = serve as-is (proxy rewrite, URL unchanged in browser)
# =============================================================================

# ── Static assets ── serve directly, NEVER pass through clean-URL lookup ──────
# These must stay here to prevent Cloudflare treating them as page routes.

/og-image.png          /og-image.png           200
/og-image.jpg          /og-image.jpg           200
/favicon.ico           /favicon.ico            200
/favicon.png           /favicon.png            200
/manifest.json         /manifest.json          200
/robots.txt            /robots.txt             200
/sitemap.xml           /sitemap.xml            200
/sitemap-*.xml         /sitemap-:splat.xml     200
/ads.txt               /ads.txt                200
/sw.js                 /sw.js                  200
/version.json          /version.json           200
/security.txt          /security.txt           200

# Asset directories — never intercept with routing logic
/assets/*              /assets/:splat          200
/public/*              /public/:splat          200
/data/*                /data/:splat            200
/images/*              /images/:splat          200
/fonts/*               /fonts/:splat           200

# ── NO page-specific rules ── Cloudflare Pages clean-URL (step ③) handles:
#   /about              → about.html
#   /services           → services.html
#   /tools              → tools.html
#   /intel              → intel.html
#   /booking            → booking.html
#   /contact            → contact.html
#   /academy            → academy.html
#   /soc-dashboard      → soc-dashboard.html
#   /privacy-policy     → privacy-policy.html      ← was causing ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS
#   /terms-of-service   → terms-of-service.html
#   /refund-policy      → refund-policy.html
#   /user-dashboard     → user-dashboard.html      ← was causing ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS
#   /admin-payments     → admin-payments.html
#
# ── NO SPA catch-all (/* /index.html 200) ──
#   Removing this allows step ③ to fire for all page clean-URLs.
#   Truly unknown routes return Cloudflare's standard 404 — acceptable for
#   a multi-page static site. All internal navigation uses .html hrefs.
